  "description": "A thirst-quenching lime and maple beverage you&#x27;ll want to sip on all summer. ",
  "headline": "Recipe: Maple Limeade",
  "HowtoTip": {
    "text": "Storage: Refrigerate for up to 1 week. Make ahead: Combine the lime juice, maple syrup, and salt to make limeade concentrate. Freeze in ice cube trays until solid. When ready to use, move the frozen cubes of limeade concentrate to a pitcher. Add 1 cup of warm water and stir until the cubes melt. Pour in the remaining 2 1/2 cups of cold water, stir, and chill. "
